text: Bilal Hassani (born 9 September 1999) is a French-Moroccan singer and YouTuber. Hassani is genderqueer and was described by French media as an "icon for French LGBT youth". == Eurovision Song Contest == She won the final of Destination Eurovision. As a prize, she represented France in the Eurovision Song Contest 2019 by singing "Roi". She finished in 16th place out of 26 finalists.
